06473nam a22009375i 9783035607154DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20172019sz     fo  d z      eng d  a(OCoLC)984546976  a97830356071547 a10.1515/97830356071542doi  a(DE-B1597)459687  a(OCoLC)980846678  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 7aARC0200002bisacsh04a720.95222300aEncounters and Positions :bArchitecture in Japan /ced. by Susanne Kohte, Hubertus Adam, Daniel Hubert. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2017] 4c©2019  a1 online resource (272 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tArchitecture in Japan: Perceptions, developments and interconnections -- tEncounters -- tFumihiko Maki -- tToyo Ito -- tOsamu Ishiyama -- tRyoji Suzuki -- tRiken Yamamoto -- tHiroaki Kimura -- tMakoto Sei Watanabe -- tJun Aoki -- tHiroshi Nakao -- tSou Fujimoto -- tRyuji Nakamura -- tJunya Ishigami -- tGo Hasegawa -- tPositions -- tCultural translations: Japanese architecture between East and West -- tThe Japanese contribution to modern architecture in Europe -- tBetween tradition and modernity: The two sides of Japanese pre-war architecture -- tThe traumas of modernization: Architecture in Japan after 1945 -- tJapan’s architectural system -- tReferences to traditions in contemporary architecture in Japan -- tAppendix -- tEditors and authors -- tIndex of names -- tIllustration credits -- tAcknowledgments0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDas Buch gibt einen Überblick über die aktuelle japanische Architektur, ihre Gestaltungskonzepte sowie ihre vielfältigen Bezüge. Dreizehn Architekten stellen in Interviews und anhand exemplarischer Entwürfe ihre Entwurfsmethodologien vor und geben Einblicke in die Grundlagen und Hintergründe ihres Schaffens; darunter junge Architekten, die aktuell international Bekanntheit erlangt haben, Architekten, die innerhalb der japanischen Architektur eigenständige Haltungen vertreten, sowie die Pritzkerpreisträger Toyo Ito und Fumihiko Maki.Das Buch zeigt, wie sich die Architekten auf Ästhetik, Raumkonzeptionen sowie Tradition in Japan - und ausserhalb - beziehen. Darüber hinaus vermitteln sechs ergänzende Texte Grundlagen und Geschichte der japanischen Architektur.  aNow as before, Japanese architecture is very popular in Europe and the western world. This publication provides an overview of its many design concepts and cross-references. Using design examples and interviews, the book presents thirteen current positions.The publication focuses on young architects who take up extremely independent positions within Japanese architecture, as well as on Pritzker Prize winners Toyo Ito and Fumihiko Maki. Six essays by European specialists on Japan provide supplementary insights into the aesthetics and space concepts of Japanese architecture, making cross-references to Japan’s architectural history, and explaining current lines of development. The book thus combines a self-reflective approach with an outsider’s analytical view.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aArchitektur. 4aJapan. 4aRaumkonzeption. 7aARCHITECTURE / Regional.2bisacsh1 aAdam, Hubertus , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAdam, Hubertus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBonnin, Philippe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFukuda-Noennig, Yoco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGleiter, Jörg H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHubert, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHubert, Daniel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/voc